{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.12"]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"title":"Migrating to 1.12","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library introduced 1 new","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"API, as well as beta support for Swift Testing.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tools of version 1.11. See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"},{"type":"text","text":" for more information."}]}],"type":"aside","style":"important"},{"text":"Custom file storage coding","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Custom-file-storage-coding"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Version 1.10 of the Composable Architecture introduced a powerful tool for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"sharing state","type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"sharing state"}]},{"text":" amongst your features, and included several built-in persistence","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"strategies, including file storage. This strategy, however, was not very flexible, and only","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"supported the default JSON encoding and decoding offered by Swift.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In this version, you can now define custom encoding and decoding logic using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"fileStorage(_:decode:encode:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Swift Testing","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Swift-Testing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Xcode 16 and Swift 6 come with a powerful new native testing framework. Existing test targets using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"XCTest can even incrementally adopt the framework and define new tests with Testing. Existing XCTest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"test ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"helpers"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", however, are not compatible with the new framework, and so test tools like the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Composable Architecture’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"TestStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" did not work with it out of the box.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"That changes with this version, which seamlessly supports XCTest ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"and","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" Swift’s Testing framework.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can now create a test store in a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Test"},{"text":" and failures will be reported accordingly.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/Compo